RAG stands for Retrieval-Augmented Generation.
RAG is a method that combines information retrieval with text generation.
A retriever finds relevant documents, and a generator produces an answer based on them.
Precision is the proportion of retrieved documents that are relevant.
Recall is the proportion of relevant documents that are successfully retrieved.
If document chunks are too small, important context may be split apart.
If document chunks are too large, irrelevant information may be included.